attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 1
attributes.caption: It's all in good fun. For now.
attributes.description: It all begins here. The boys begin their slow march towards competitive Overwatch greatness. Or a very quick march towards the end of their friendships. Either way it should be pretty entertaining.

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 2
attributes.caption: We're not saying we're the best Overwatch players ever, but...
attributes.description: Everyone is so happy! It's all high-fives and back-pats in the Funhaus offices. There's no way this embarrassment of victories will ever end! Right?

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 3
attributes.caption: The cracks are starting to show.
attributes.description: I wish I cared about anything as much as these guys care about Overwatch. Sorry, Honey.

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 4
attributes.caption: "You should always play with warm hands."
attributes.description: In this week's episode, Lawrence seriously considers tracking down an 11 year old and murdering him for talking too much.

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 5
attributes.caption: "I figure we're supposed to, like, be getting good, right?"
attributes.description: Sorry to get your hopes up, but the Official Funhaus Branded eSports Towel a.k.a. The FunSham is currently out of stock.

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 6
attributes.caption: Mmmm... so salty.
attributes.description:
If any of you out there had rough childhoods, you might want to watch something else. Mommy and Daddy fight A LOT in this one.

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 7
attributes.caption: "Overwatch is a game based on trust."
attributes.description:
Is this it?! Is this the turning point? Is this the moment when these four men come together as a team and finally crush the competition? How the hell should I know? Get off my back. I just work here.

attributes.title: OVERWATCH COMPETITIVE Ep. 8
attributes.caption: "I don't have a lot of faith in any of you."
attributes.description:
It all comes down to this. Will our boys bind together as a team to crush the competition? Or will they squabble and scream until they all quit to start their own gaming channels in opposite corners of the same room, hanging sheets to separate their territories like Marsha and Greg Brady sharing the attic apartment? Ask your parents.
